title._content: #   Line up of Curtiss Jennys at Rockwell Field, NI

description._content: A line up of seven Curtiss JN-4 Jennys aircraft at the Army's Rockwell Field on North Island. The first two Jennys are equipped with the 150hp French Hispano-Suiza engine built in the US as the Wright Model A. These models were used by the Navy as the Curtiss N-9 single float primary trainer. The other Jennys are the JH-4H models powered by the 150hp Wiright-Hispano engine, popularly called the Hisso. circa 1918-1919 McCellan AFB archives North Island collection From History of Naval Aviation Collection Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
